title: Cross sections for the proton-induced production of He and Ne isotopes from magnesium, aluminum and silicon.

x4freetext: Cross sections for the proton-induced production of He
and Ne isotopes from magnesium, aluminum and silicon.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.145, p.449 (1998)
Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Data for Sci. and Technology, Nice 2007, Vol.2, p.1061 (2007)

x4freetext: Data were revised for Subents
About mini-stack.
AVF Cyclotron,Paul Scherrer Institut,
Fixed Energy Isochronous Cyclotron.
Below 50 MeV.
For all irradiation experiments with proton energies
above 200 MeV so-called mini-stack-approach was used
instead of the well known stacked-foil-technique.
Total uncertainty. The errors given for the
cross sections include:
uncertainties of the mass and thickness of
the target foil which are commonly less than 1%.
The additional error due to uncertainties of
the measurements of the monitoring radionuclides,
Na-22 and Zn-65,can be regarded to be about 2%.
The noble gas concentrations were reproducible
within 2%  and
the absolute gas amounts are accurate within 5%
Fluctuations in the beam intensity during the
irradiation were taken into account when calculating
flux densities and cross sections and they resulted
in an overall error of less than 1% for the product
nuclides presented here.
.The Uncertainty is Reported by Authors.
All considered errors added up quadratically
to the uncertainties given in tables.
* The error resulting from recoil and cross
contamination cancel out when analyzing the foils in
the middle of each target element unit.
* The error of the cross sections used for beam
monitoring were not taken into account when calculating
the uncertainties of the final results.
.Time gaps between end of irradiation and mass
spectrometric analysis (days).
Last checking has been done.
DATE in Subents 002, 008 and 014 were
revised by authors.
SD: page in ref. on 2007NICE corrected;
Entry corrected according to last EXFOR rules and Dict.
Small stacks of high purity foils were used.
The Mg-foils with typical thicknesses of 0.1 mm;
specified purities of 99.9%.
Data were revised considering now H-3 diffusive losses
and new information for the H-3/He-3 branching ratios
was made.
Table 1 from 2007NICE,2,1061,2007 -revised data
